1
00:00:36,933 --> 00:00:40,100
<i>Good thing I was never part
of your family.</i>

2
00:00:40,233 --> 00:00:44,600
<i>I don't need rude,
unforgiving siblings!</i>

3
00:00:45,667 --> 00:00:47,167
<i> Coleen! That's enough!</i>

4
00:00:47,300 --> 00:00:48,667
<i>Did you really have
to make a scene today?</i>

5
00:00:48,800 --> 00:00:50,300
<i> Aren't you even embarrassed?</i>

6
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:52,900
<i>Don't you ever get tired
of all the fighting?</i>

7
00:00:53,033 --> 00:00:55,700
<i>You're supposed to listen
to each other.</i>

8
00:00:55,833 --> 00:00:58,700
<i>The kid understands
better than you do.</i>

9
00:00:58,833 --> 00:00:59,667
<i> Afritada.</i>

10
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:00,633
<i> Mom sent it.</i>

11
00:01:00,767 --> 00:01:01,767
<i> I'll go ahead.</i>

12
00:01:01,900 --> 00:01:04,200
<i>Tetay and Auntie Paz
are waiting downstairs.</i>

13
00:01:04,333 --> 00:01:06,100
<i> The Sakay car waited for you?</i>

14
00:01:06,233 --> 00:01:07,400
<i> Good thing they agreed.</i>

15
00:01:07,567 --> 00:01:09,133
<i>They're not allowed to do that,
right?</i>

16
00:01:09,267 --> 00:01:11,033
<i> Oh, your car's been returned.</i>

17
00:01:11,167 --> 00:01:12,433
<i>Look, I'm leaving.
You can scold me later.</i>

18
00:01:12,567 --> 00:01:14,167
<i> And you left this. Keep it!</i>

19
00:01:14,300 --> 00:01:15,733
<i>- It's really for you.
- I don't want it!</i>

20
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:16,867
<i>It's so you'll have something
to eat.</i>

21
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:19,467
<i>What's with the drama now,
Manuel?</i>

22
00:01:19,600 --> 00:01:20,733
<i> Manuel, why are you crying?</i>

23
00:01:20,867 --> 00:01:21,933
<i> Here comes the mistress.</i>

24
00:01:22,067 --> 00:01:24,267
<i>Jessica and I should've left
a long time ago.</i>

25
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,633
<i> Don't.</i>

26
00:01:25,767 --> 00:01:28,200
<i>You really used your own kids
to keep Manuel tied to you?</i>

27
00:01:28,333 --> 00:01:29,633
<i> Felma, wait!</i>

28
00:01:29,767 --> 00:01:31,167
<i> Mom, what's wrong?</i>

29
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:33,933
<i> Your dad and Felma...</i>

30
00:01:34,067 --> 00:01:35,833
<i> they're having an affair.</i>

31
00:01:40,767 --> 00:01:42,067
No, this can't be true.

32
00:01:42,200 --> 00:01:44,433
Dad and Aunt Felma
would never do this.

33
00:01:45,867 --> 00:01:47,233
So I was right all along.

34
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:51,267
Your dad really wants to get
back with his mistress.

35
00:01:53,400 --> 00:01:55,200
But where did you get this?

36
00:01:56,467 --> 00:01:57,567
How?

37
00:01:58,633 --> 00:01:59,867
Mom,

38
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:03,567
did you plant a hidden camera
in Aunt Felma's house?

39
00:02:03,700 --> 00:02:05,433
Yes!

40
00:02:05,567 --> 00:02:07,433
I did it so I could catch them.

41
00:02:08,500 --> 00:02:10,700
Right?

42
00:02:10,833 --> 00:02:13,067
You can see the evidence.

43
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,033
They're cheating on me.

44
00:02:16,800 --> 00:02:18,933
Mom, what you do is illegal.

45
00:02:19,067 --> 00:02:21,433
Illegal or not,

46
00:02:21,567 --> 00:02:23,433
the important thing is...

47
00:02:23,567 --> 00:02:27,033
I proved my suspicions.

48
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:28,900
I'll find more evidence.

49
00:02:30,100 --> 00:02:32,400
I'll sue them.

50
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:33,500
Mom, please.

51
00:02:34,867 --> 00:02:36,433
I don't want Dad to go to jail.

52
00:02:36,567 --> 00:02:37,833
Please, Mom.

53
00:02:37,967 --> 00:02:39,533
- Please.
- Then help me.

54
00:02:42,833 --> 00:02:44,700
Dear, let's separate them.

55
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,000
Help me.

56
00:02:50,600 --> 00:02:52,833
You'll help me, right?

57
00:02:52,967 --> 00:02:55,800
We've talked about leaving,
but Mom...

58
00:02:55,933 --> 00:02:57,867
Don't just talk about it.

59
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,133
Do something!

60
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:02,967
Move out of Felma's house.

61
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:06,067
Leave now, dear, or else...

62
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:10,067
I'm sorry, Jessica.

63
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:13,333
I'll do whatever it takes

64
00:03:13,467 --> 00:03:15,567
to put your dad behind bars.

65
00:03:20,967 --> 00:03:22,267
Everything's ready.

66
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:30,233
Who are you talking to?

67
00:03:30,367 --> 00:03:32,633
It's my team leader.

68
00:03:32,767 --> 00:03:34,533
Is Tetay dressed already?

69
00:03:34,667 --> 00:03:36,067
She's in the bathroom.

70
00:03:37,867 --> 00:03:39,067
Daisy, wait a sec.

71
00:03:42,167 --> 00:03:45,567
You know, we haven't talked
in days. Since Sunday, I think.

72
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:46,733
Is something wrong?

73
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:49,100
What?

74
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:51,167
Nothing.

75
00:03:51,300 --> 00:03:53,933
My schedule's just been
all over the place.

76
00:03:54,100 --> 00:03:55,867
We're handling a new account.

77
00:03:57,600 --> 00:03:59,800
You know, maybe it's time
you leave that job.

78
00:04:01,200 --> 00:04:03,467
Do you want to try FMP?
I can talk to Mom for you.

79
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,233
Oh no, it's okay.

80
00:04:05,367 --> 00:04:07,733
I'm fine where I am.

81
00:04:07,867 --> 00:04:09,633
My schedule's getting better,
too.

82
00:04:11,833 --> 00:04:13,367
Are you sure?

83
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:15,433
Don't we have any problems?

84
00:04:15,567 --> 00:04:17,267
None, Jeff.

85
00:04:17,400 --> 00:04:18,867
We're good.

86
00:04:34,167 --> 00:04:35,567
<i> Felma, wait.</i>

87
00:04:39,500 --> 00:04:41,833
<i>- Are you pregnant?
- Yes.</i>

88
00:04:41,967 --> 00:04:43,600
<i> Yes!</i>

89
00:04:43,733 --> 00:04:45,367
<i> We're having a baby!</i>

90
00:04:45,500 --> 00:04:48,633
<i>Don't be so loud,
it's embarrassing.</i>

91
00:04:48,767 --> 00:04:49,833
<i> Love.</i>

92
00:04:49,967 --> 00:04:52,267
<i>I already know
what we'll name our child.</i>

93
00:04:52,400 --> 00:04:53,500
<i> What?</i>

94
00:04:53,633 --> 00:04:54,967
<i> Felmo.</i>

95
00:04:55,100 --> 00:04:56,500
<i> Felmo?</i>

96
00:04:56,633 --> 00:04:57,933
<i> Sounds kinda odd.</i>

97
00:04:58,067 --> 00:05:00,067
<i> I want him to take after you.</i>

98
00:05:00,200 --> 00:05:04,233
<i>Hardworking, kind, and caring.
I love you so much.</i>

99
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:06,200
<i> Of course, I love you too.</i>

100
00:05:07,433 --> 00:05:10,333
<i>Manuel! Mr. Bert's jeep is here,
Manuel.</i>

101
00:05:10,467 --> 00:05:12,567
<i>We'll just take you to
the hospital, okay, dear?</i>

102
00:05:12,700 --> 00:05:15,600
<i>Where are we going to get
300,000 pesos, Manuel?</i>

103
00:05:15,733 --> 00:05:20,400
<i>Just for Andrea's medicine,
we're already running out.</i>

104
00:05:20,533 --> 00:05:22,333
<i> What if I work abroad?</i>

105
00:05:25,567 --> 00:05:28,233
<i>Abel's been asking me
to go for a while now.</i>

106
00:05:31,867 --> 00:05:35,333
<i>Hey, sis. Come on.
He might miss his flight.</i>

107
00:05:35,500 --> 00:05:37,700
<i> Go now.</i>

108
00:05:37,833 --> 00:05:38,867
<i> Go.</i>

109
00:05:39,000 --> 00:05:40,367
<i> Go now.</i>

110
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:49,667
Son.

111
00:05:49,800 --> 00:05:51,200
Is something wrong?

112
00:05:52,233 --> 00:05:54,367
Is this about...

113
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:55,900
the party?

114
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:00,567
No, Mom. It's...

115
00:06:00,700 --> 00:06:01,733
it's Daisy.

116
00:06:03,767 --> 00:06:05,233
It's like something's changed.

117
00:06:08,200 --> 00:06:09,167
You know, we're okay,

118
00:06:09,300 --> 00:06:11,033
but it feels like
she's not happy with me anymore.

119
00:06:13,133 --> 00:06:14,900
We barely talk properly now.

120
00:06:16,300 --> 00:06:18,900
And when I ask her what's
wrong, she won't even answer me.

121
00:06:21,967 --> 00:06:23,733
You know, this isn't
what I expected.

122
00:06:26,033 --> 00:06:27,567
I thought
that once we were together,

123
00:06:27,700 --> 00:06:29,833
we'd be happy, and everything
would fall into place.

124
00:06:31,933 --> 00:06:33,567
Like...

125
00:06:34,567 --> 00:06:35,933
Like what?

126
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:39,533
Like you and...

127
00:06:41,400 --> 00:06:42,933
your ex.

128
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,167
You were still happy, even
when things were falling apart.

129
00:06:54,100 --> 00:06:55,867
You talked about everything.

130
00:06:57,233 --> 00:06:58,600
You were always
on the same team.

131
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:00,700
No matter how hard life got,

132
00:07:03,167 --> 00:07:05,000
you faced it together.

133
00:07:07,367 --> 00:07:10,200
You supported each other
through everything.

134
00:07:10,333 --> 00:07:13,500
I think that's what I've
been looking for with Daisy,

135
00:07:13,633 --> 00:07:15,033
but I just don't see it.

136
00:07:17,133 --> 00:07:18,767
Son,

137
00:07:18,900 --> 00:07:22,467
every relationship
goes through things like that.

138
00:07:24,767 --> 00:07:26,900
You and Daisy are still new.

139
00:07:27,033 --> 00:07:28,900
Don't rush it.

140
00:07:29,033 --> 00:07:30,533
Things will work
out in time, son.

141
00:07:32,200 --> 00:07:33,633
I hope so, Mom.

142
00:07:42,767 --> 00:07:45,033
I've started packing, Hyacinth.

143
00:07:45,167 --> 00:07:47,600
<i> How about your passports?</i>

144
00:07:47,767 --> 00:07:48,933
<i> My niece's school documents?</i>

145
00:07:49,067 --> 00:07:50,933
<i> Your tickets?</i>

146
00:07:51,067 --> 00:07:53,267
I've secured everything.

147
00:07:53,400 --> 00:07:55,767
<i>Are you really not
going to tell Jeffrey?</i>

148
00:08:03,000 --> 00:08:04,867
No, sis.

149
00:08:05,000 --> 00:08:07,567
He wasn't even part of our lives

150
00:08:07,700 --> 00:08:09,433
when we started
planning all this.

151
00:08:09,567 --> 00:08:11,333
<i>But he's the father
of your child.</i>

152
00:08:11,467 --> 00:08:13,433
<i> He has a right to Tetay, too.</i>

153
00:08:13,567 --> 00:08:15,767
<i> Why won't you just tell him?</i>

154
00:08:15,900 --> 00:08:17,733
Because he won't agree.

155
00:08:18,867 --> 00:08:21,067
I asked him before

156
00:08:21,233 --> 00:08:23,400
if he'd be okay with us

157
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:26,100
building a life abroad.

158
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,433
He said no.

159
00:08:29,567 --> 00:08:32,300
<i> Well then, it's your decision.</i>

160
00:08:32,433 --> 00:08:34,300
It's not my place to interfere.

161
00:08:34,433 --> 00:08:36,667
<i>Just give me a call
when you're ready.</i>

162
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:18,667
Jessica?

163
00:09:18,800 --> 00:09:19,900
What's that?

164
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,767
What are you doing?

165
00:09:24,900 --> 00:09:26,100
Coleen.

166
00:09:28,033 --> 00:09:29,833
Hidden cam?

167
00:09:32,233 --> 00:09:33,633
Jessica, what is this?

168
00:09:34,900 --> 00:09:38,833
Why are you puttin up hiddeen
cameras? Are you spying on us?

169
00:09:38,967 --> 00:09:40,200
Why...

170
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:45,333
Did your mom tell you
to do that?

171
00:09:46,700 --> 00:09:48,533
Didang!

172
00:09:48,667 --> 00:09:49,900
Didang!

173
00:09:50,033 --> 00:09:51,533
Hey.

174
00:09:51,667 --> 00:09:53,233
What's going on?

175
00:09:53,367 --> 00:09:55,133
Why are you shouting?

176
00:09:55,267 --> 00:09:57,200
Call Mom, please.

177
00:09:57,333 --> 00:09:58,767
I have no load.

178
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,600
Why?

179
00:10:00,733 --> 00:10:01,900
Coleen, why? What happened?

180
00:10:02,067 --> 00:10:03,067
Dad.

181
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:06,933
Dad, your daughter is putting up
hidden cameras here.

182
00:10:08,367 --> 00:10:10,233
Jessica, why did you do that?

183
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:12,300
Coleen, why? What happened?

184
00:10:12,433 --> 00:10:14,133
- Dad...
- Dad,

185
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:17,100
your daughter is putting up
hidden cameras here.

186
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:19,800
Jessica, why did you do that?

187
00:10:22,000 --> 00:10:23,100
Jessica!

188
00:10:25,167 --> 00:10:26,467
Jessica,
I'm still talking to you!

189
00:10:26,600 --> 00:10:27,833
Open the door!

190
00:10:33,667 --> 00:10:34,733
Yes, Mom.

191
00:10:34,900 --> 00:10:36,867
I caught her in the act.

192
00:10:37,000 --> 00:10:38,700
Calm down, dear.

193
00:10:38,833 --> 00:10:40,633
I don't understand.

194
00:10:42,667 --> 00:10:44,167
A hidden camera?

195
00:10:44,300 --> 00:10:45,367
Yes, Mom.

196
00:10:45,500 --> 00:10:49,933
I caught Jessica placing a
hidden cam in the plants.

197
00:10:50,067 --> 00:10:51,433
All right, I'm coming home.

198
00:10:52,667 --> 00:10:53,533
But listen.

199
00:10:53,667 --> 00:10:55,200
Try to control yourself, dear.

200
00:10:55,333 --> 00:10:57,200
Don't fight with your sister.

201
00:10:57,333 --> 00:10:59,100
Coleen, answer me!

202
00:10:59,233 --> 00:11:00,567
I won't.

203
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:09,600
Wait a minute.

204
00:11:21,300 --> 00:11:22,233
Truce?

205
00:11:23,267 --> 00:11:25,500
Sorry about what happened
last time, okay?

206
00:11:26,900 --> 00:11:28,767
I was just "hangry".

207
00:11:28,900 --> 00:11:31,800
So now you're just angry?

208
00:11:31,933 --> 00:11:34,233
You know what, come in.
Perfect timing.

209
00:11:34,367 --> 00:11:36,533
Come in, please. Sit down.

210
00:11:36,667 --> 00:11:38,867
My brunch today is amazing.

211
00:11:44,333 --> 00:11:46,133
Afritada...

212
00:11:47,600 --> 00:11:48,967
à la Felma.

213
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:52,533
How did...

214
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:54,400
I ran into your brother
last night.

215
00:11:54,533 --> 00:11:55,333
He said you turned it down.

216
00:11:55,467 --> 00:11:56,200
So I asked for it instead.

217
00:11:56,333 --> 00:11:58,633
It's such a waste
not to try it.

218
00:11:58,767 --> 00:12:01,167
You know what...

219
00:12:01,300 --> 00:12:02,300
come on, sit down.

220
00:12:02,433 --> 00:12:04,700
I'll put this on the table.
Let's go, let's go!

221
00:12:30,767 --> 00:12:31,733
Chill.

222
00:12:31,867 --> 00:12:34,200
I won't force you.

223
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:36,267
If you don't want it,

224
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:39,500
there's adobo
that Lilet brought.

225
00:12:53,033 --> 00:12:54,533
Let's eat.

226
00:13:10,967 --> 00:13:12,667
You know what, you know what...

227
00:13:17,233 --> 00:13:19,900
Are you sure?
Won't you even try even a bit?

228
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:27,933
You were right.

229
00:13:28,067 --> 00:13:30,067
Frying the potatoes makes it
taste so much better.

230
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:31,733
Your mom's amazing.

231
00:13:35,200 --> 00:13:36,400
So good.

232
00:13:51,633 --> 00:13:52,900
Water.

233
00:14:13,733 --> 00:14:16,500
Don't let my brother find out,
okay?

234
00:14:16,633 --> 00:14:18,400
This stays between us.

235
00:14:18,533 --> 00:14:19,400
Come on, eat more.

236
00:14:19,533 --> 00:14:20,833
Have some more rice.

237
00:14:25,767 --> 00:14:26,967
Delicious.

238
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:35,733
Jessica!

239
00:14:35,867 --> 00:14:36,900
Jessica!

240
00:14:38,467 --> 00:14:39,967
Jessica, open the door!

241
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:42,900
Sir. Manuel, here.
Here's the master key.

242
00:14:47,000 --> 00:14:48,400
Jessica!

243
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:52,033
Why do you have
a hidden camera?

244
00:14:52,167 --> 00:14:54,700
Dad, it's not mine. It's Mom's!

245
00:14:54,833 --> 00:14:57,500
You've been caught, and
you're still denying it?

246
00:14:58,400 --> 00:15:00,933
Dad, I'm telling
the truth!

247
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,600
Then whose is it?

248
00:15:02,733 --> 00:15:04,700
- Your mom's?
- Yes!

249
00:15:05,767 --> 00:15:07,467
Why?

250
00:15:07,600 --> 00:15:09,767
Did she tell you to do it?

251
00:15:09,900 --> 00:15:11,833
No, Dad.

252
00:15:11,967 --> 00:15:15,767
Mom was the one who planted it.
I was going to remove it.

253
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:19,000
Then how did you even
know there was a camera?

254
00:15:21,600 --> 00:15:23,433
Did you meet
with your mom?

255
00:15:24,367 --> 00:15:25,867
Yes.

256
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:28,233
She said she had
something to tell me.

257
00:15:29,367 --> 00:15:30,633
And then...

258
00:15:30,767 --> 00:15:33,367
she showed me a video of you...

259
00:15:33,500 --> 00:15:35,933
and Aunt Felma

260
00:15:36,100 --> 00:15:37,467
kissing.

261
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,200
She sent me a copy.

262
00:15:50,533 --> 00:15:52,700
Was Mom right?

263
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,233
Are you having an affair?

264
00:15:54,367 --> 00:15:57,167
Is Aunt Felma
your mistress?

265
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:58,567
What did you say?

266
00:16:03,133 --> 00:16:04,833
My mom is not a mistress.

267
00:16:04,967 --> 00:16:06,267
- Coleen!
- Take back what you said!

268
00:16:06,400 --> 00:16:08,100
Coleen, that's enough! Coleen!

269
00:16:08,267 --> 00:16:09,700
- Take that back!
- Jessica!

270
00:16:09,833 --> 00:16:10,767
- Let go of me!
- Take that back!

271
00:16:10,900 --> 00:16:12,700
- Coleen, stop!
- Jessica!

272
00:16:12,833 --> 00:16:14,567
- Coleen!
- I said let go of me!

273
00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:16,600
- Jessica, stop!
- Let go of me!

274
00:16:16,733 --> 00:16:19,500
Jessica, stop!

275
00:16:19,633 --> 00:16:21,867
- Let go of me!
- Jessica!

276
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:23,200
- Hey!
- Jessica!

277
00:16:24,733 --> 00:16:26,900
You're so stubborn!

278
00:16:27,033 --> 00:16:30,500
I told you not to fight
with your sister!

279
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,733
I didn't want to, Mom!

280
00:16:33,867 --> 00:16:36,133
But she called you a mistress!

281
00:16:46,867 --> 00:16:49,833
I don't need
to watch that video.

282
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:51,233
I know the truth.

283
00:16:51,367 --> 00:16:53,500
And Manuel knows
what really happened.

284
00:16:54,733 --> 00:16:56,933
I'm not your dad's mistress,
Jessica.

285
00:16:58,200 --> 00:17:00,400
There's nothing going on
between me and Manuel.

286
00:17:01,433 --> 00:17:03,000
What she's saying is true.

287
00:17:04,767 --> 00:17:08,100
I was just comforting your
dad that night

288
00:17:09,800 --> 00:17:11,133
because of everything he was
going through with your brother,

289
00:17:11,267 --> 00:17:12,467
Jeffrey.

290
00:17:13,700 --> 00:17:15,533
And then...

291
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:18,667
when I said goodbye,
he accidentally pulled me in.

292
00:17:18,800 --> 00:17:19,967
That's all.

293
00:17:20,100 --> 00:17:22,467
It's your mom who's
being malicious.

294
00:17:22,600 --> 00:17:25,467
She even edited the video
of Mom and Dad

295
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:27,433
to make it appear as though
they were kissing.

296
00:17:27,567 --> 00:17:29,400
And you actually
believed her?

297
00:17:29,533 --> 00:17:31,767
You accused my mom
of being a mistress.

298
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:33,767
You're just as malicious.

299
00:17:33,900 --> 00:17:36,000
I didn't call Aunt Felma
a mistress.

300
00:17:36,133 --> 00:17:37,367
I was asking Dad.

301
00:17:38,367 --> 00:17:40,467
Asking is different
from accusing.

302
00:17:40,600 --> 00:17:43,667
Whether you asked or accused,

303
00:17:43,800 --> 00:17:47,200
you still thought
Felma was my mistress.

304
00:17:47,333 --> 00:17:49,800
And I won't let
you call her that!

305
00:17:49,967 --> 00:17:51,600
Manuel,

306
00:17:51,733 --> 00:17:53,500
don't raise your voice
at your daughter.

307
00:17:54,567 --> 00:17:57,100
I'm sorry, dear,
but I didn't like what you did.

308
00:17:58,667 --> 00:17:59,700
Say sorry.

309
00:18:02,600 --> 00:18:04,333
I'm sorry, Aunt Felma.

310
00:18:05,400 --> 00:18:07,100
I'm so sorry.

311
00:18:11,233 --> 00:18:12,467
Manuel,

312
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,233
Coleen, Didang...

313
00:18:14,367 --> 00:18:16,700
Please leave Jessica
and me alone for now.

314
00:18:35,833 --> 00:18:37,367
Hi, Ma'am. Good evening.

315
00:18:47,300 --> 00:18:48,867
Why is there no signal?

316
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,967
Jessica?

317
00:19:05,300 --> 00:19:06,933
Jessica!

318
00:19:25,633 --> 00:19:27,433
I'm not angry at you, Jessica.

319
00:19:29,833 --> 00:19:31,700
Just disappointed.

320
00:19:33,933 --> 00:19:35,267
But I understand you.

321
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:38,467
You were only asking a question.

322
00:19:40,233 --> 00:19:42,500
But Dad was right, Auntie.

323
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,800
I still entertained the thought.

324
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:51,233
Because that's
what your mom believes.

325
00:19:52,567 --> 00:19:54,933
And she keeps putting
that in your head.

326
00:19:57,233 --> 00:19:59,033
But let me say it
again, Jessica.

327
00:20:00,667 --> 00:20:02,833
There is nothing
between me and Manuel.

328
00:20:05,200 --> 00:20:07,500
I'm sorry, Aunt Felma.

329
00:20:08,500 --> 00:20:10,267
I'm really, really sorry.

330
00:20:12,133 --> 00:20:13,067
It's okay.

331
00:20:14,300 --> 00:20:16,300
We're good now.

332
00:20:16,433 --> 00:20:17,533
Thank you.

333
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:19,633
Thank you.

334
00:20:21,033 --> 00:20:22,200
There, there.

335
00:20:22,333 --> 00:20:24,033
It's okay, Jessica.

336
00:20:26,067 --> 00:20:27,667
It's okay now, dear.

337
00:20:52,467 --> 00:20:53,700
Mommy.

338
00:20:56,433 --> 00:20:58,700
Good thing you came.

339
00:20:58,833 --> 00:21:00,633
I thought
you weren't going to show up.

340
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:02,900
So?

341
00:21:05,200 --> 00:21:07,467
Where's the spy camera?

342
00:21:07,600 --> 00:21:08,300
Give it to me.

343
00:21:08,467 --> 00:21:10,233
Is this what you're
looking for?

344
00:21:14,367 --> 00:21:15,800
Traitor!

345
00:21:15,933 --> 00:21:17,033
Stop it.

346
00:21:17,167 --> 00:21:18,100
- Wait!
- Mommy, stop!

347
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:19,267
Aunt Felma!

348
00:21:19,400 --> 00:21:22,367
Stop your evilness, Hazel!

349
00:21:22,500 --> 00:21:24,933
I'll sue you for
wiretapping,

350
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:28,167
data privacy violations,
and photo and video voyeurism!

351
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:31,400
And I'll add your sabotage
of FMP to the charges!

352
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:38,133
I wasn't informed.

353
00:21:38,267 --> 00:21:40,467
What is this, a contest to
see who can file the most cases?

354
00:21:40,600 --> 00:21:42,400
A contest?

355
00:21:42,567 --> 00:21:44,033
I only have one
case against you.

356
00:21:45,433 --> 00:21:47,500
Concubinage.

357
00:21:47,633 --> 00:21:50,400
I'll have the man you're
obsessed with thrown in jail.

358
00:21:50,533 --> 00:21:52,067
And you?

359
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:54,100
I'll make you famous...

360
00:21:54,233 --> 00:21:56,400
on social media.

361
00:21:56,533 --> 00:21:58,933
I'll brand you as the
nation's number-one mistress

362
00:21:59,067 --> 00:22:03,533
- and make Flirty Felma trend!
-Will you please shut up, Mommy?

363
00:22:03,667 --> 00:22:05,100
I brought Aunt Felma here

364
00:22:05,233 --> 00:22:08,100
so you could talk
and end this threat.

365
00:22:09,500 --> 00:22:11,633
And Dad told me the truth.

366
00:22:11,767 --> 00:22:13,267
There's no relationship
between them.

367
00:22:13,400 --> 00:22:14,700
No! You shut up!

368
00:22:15,833 --> 00:22:17,633
You're getting on my nerves,
Jessica!

369
00:22:18,700 --> 00:22:20,833
Why are you siding
with that woman?

370
00:22:20,967 --> 00:22:22,200
What did she feed you, huh?

371
00:22:22,333 --> 00:22:24,300
A truckload of longganisa?

372
00:22:24,433 --> 00:22:26,100
- Come here!
- Wait!

373
00:22:27,100 --> 00:22:28,533
Hazel, stop it!

374
00:22:28,667 --> 00:22:29,400
Stop it!

375
00:22:29,533 --> 00:22:30,633
- Let go of me!
- Mom!

376
00:22:30,767 --> 00:22:31,700
Mom!

377
00:22:31,833 --> 00:22:36,300
- What?
- Mom, stop it!

378
00:22:36,433 --> 00:22:37,400
Let go of me!

379
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:38,967
Let go of me!

380
00:22:39,100 --> 00:22:40,600
You're the reason our
family is broken!

381
00:22:40,733 --> 00:22:43,300
You're insane!

382
00:22:43,433 --> 00:22:46,233
You're the insane one! You're
even hurting your own child!

383
00:22:46,367 --> 00:22:47,233
Let go of me!

384
00:22:47,367 --> 00:22:48,533
Stop it already!

385
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,833
Whatever!

386
00:22:50,967 --> 00:22:52,733
- Let go of me!
- You can't take my child!

387
00:22:54,867 --> 00:22:55,800
Mom!

388
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:57,033
No!

389
00:22:58,567 --> 00:23:00,800
- Mom.
- No!

390
00:23:00,933 --> 00:23:02,233
Mom, I'm sorry.

391
00:23:05,433 --> 00:23:08,733
Are you choosing
that woman over me?

392
00:23:08,867 --> 00:23:10,600
Mom, sorry.

393
00:23:10,733 --> 00:23:12,633
I'm your mother, Jessica.

394
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:14,600
But you've gone too far!

395
00:23:14,733 --> 00:23:16,500
I can't take you anymore!

396
00:23:18,467 --> 00:23:19,733
Aunt Felma, let's go.

397
00:23:19,867 --> 00:23:21,200
Jessica, where
are you going?

398
00:23:23,333 --> 00:23:24,867
Jessica!

399
00:23:41,600 --> 00:23:43,000
I'm sorry, Manuel.

400
00:23:44,267 --> 00:23:47,000
I shouldn't have
forced Jessica...

401
00:23:47,133 --> 00:23:49,100
to meet with her mom.

402
00:23:51,400 --> 00:23:53,200
I shouldn't have
gone either.

403
00:23:54,367 --> 00:23:56,200
It only made things worse.

404
00:23:57,400 --> 00:23:58,700
I'm sorry, Jessica.

405
00:24:00,733 --> 00:24:03,033
It's okay.
It's not your fault, Auntie.

406
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,800
It's Mom's.

407
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:12,000
Does your neck still hurt?

408
00:24:12,133 --> 00:24:13,933
You should've
had it checked.

409
00:24:18,967 --> 00:24:19,900
I'm okay.

410
00:24:21,400 --> 00:24:23,200
Jessica saved me, anyway.

411
00:24:24,467 --> 00:24:25,800
Thank you, dear.

412
00:24:26,900 --> 00:24:29,900
But what you did
to your mom...

413
00:24:30,067 --> 00:24:31,467
was still wrong.

414
00:24:31,600 --> 00:24:33,467
You shouldn't
have pushed her.

415
00:24:33,600 --> 00:24:34,967
Don't ever do that again.

416
00:24:36,133 --> 00:24:36,767
Yes, Auntie.

417
00:24:37,633 --> 00:24:39,067
Alright.

418
00:24:39,200 --> 00:24:41,767
I'll go ahead so...

419
00:24:41,900 --> 00:24:43,733
you both can rest.

420
00:24:51,900 --> 00:24:53,200
Dad,

421
00:24:55,967 --> 00:24:57,933
I'm sorry...

422
00:24:58,067 --> 00:24:59,667
again...

423
00:24:59,800 --> 00:25:02,533
if I doubted you and Aunt Felma.

424
00:25:05,533 --> 00:25:08,400
It's okay, dear.
Don't think about it anymore.

425
00:25:28,833 --> 00:25:31,100
What I really don't understand

426
00:25:31,233 --> 00:25:33,433
is why you doubted me
and Felma in the first place.

427
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:37,533
Because I know...

428
00:25:37,700 --> 00:25:39,900
you still love Aunt Felma.

429
00:25:41,933 --> 00:25:43,100
<i> Dad,</i>

430
00:25:43,233 --> 00:25:45,933
<i>do you still
love your first wife?</i>

431
00:25:46,067 --> 00:25:47,867
Sweetie, I can't
love her anymore.

432
00:25:49,367 --> 00:25:51,133
<i> Your mom is my wife now.</i>

433
00:25:52,733 --> 00:25:55,733
I asked you before if
you still loved her.

434
00:25:55,867 --> 00:25:57,467
You didn't deny it.

435
00:25:59,367 --> 00:26:00,733
Dear,

436
00:26:00,867 --> 00:26:02,700
I didn't deny it because...

437
00:26:03,900 --> 00:26:05,667
because it's true.

438
00:26:09,533 --> 00:26:11,433
I still love Felma.

439
00:26:13,667 --> 00:26:15,133
I love her very much.

440
00:26:22,767 --> 00:26:24,633
I'm scared because...

441
00:26:24,767 --> 00:26:27,333
Mom will have you jailed

442
00:26:27,467 --> 00:26:30,033
if it's true you're having
an affair with Aunt Felma.

443
00:26:30,167 --> 00:26:32,500
Let's say,
by some divine intervention,

444
00:26:32,633 --> 00:26:34,767
you stumble upon evidence.

445
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:37,233
Only Manuel will go
to jail, not Felma.

446
00:26:37,367 --> 00:26:40,300
Do you want your own child
to curse you forever?

447
00:26:40,433 --> 00:26:42,100
I'm going to file
for an annulment.

448
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:44,000
Why would you suddenly say that?

449
00:26:44,133 --> 00:26:45,867
Because of Felma.

450
00:26:46,000 --> 00:26:47,700
I want us
to get back together.

451
00:26:47,833 --> 00:26:50,833
Don't let Felma
and Manuel reconcile.

452
00:26:50,967 --> 00:26:54,433
Because if that happens,
you'll be pushed aside.

453
00:26:54,567 --> 00:26:56,900
Jessica's already found
an apartment.

454
00:26:57,033 --> 00:26:59,167
So you've decided.

455
00:26:59,300 --> 00:27:01,800
Well, you really need
to leave here

456
00:27:01,933 --> 00:27:03,867
to finally end all this chaos.

457
00:27:04,000 --> 00:27:05,733
But Felma,
I'll come back for you.

458
00:27:05,867 --> 00:27:07,400
I'll just annul
my marriage with Hazel,

459
00:27:07,533 --> 00:27:08,700
and then I'll come back to you.

460
00:27:08,833 --> 00:27:10,567
Felma, you're the one I love.

461
00:27:10,700 --> 00:27:13,067
You were the one I loved
then, you're the one I love now.

462
00:27:13,200 --> 00:27:15,367
You're the one
I'll love forever.
